[L. A. No. 2483. Department One. June 13, 1910.] JOHN H. ENGEBRETSEN, Respondent, v. JOHN H. GAY et al., Appellants. Street Assessment—Valid Contract—Damage by Contractor—Publication.—Held, in this case, that the same questions are involved as in the ease of Gay v. Engebretsen, (L. A. No. 2455), ante, p. 21, [109 Pae. 876] ; and the judgment in this ease is affirmed on the authority of that case. APPEAL from a judgment of the Superior Court of San Diego County. W. R. Guy, Judge. The facts are the same as those involved in L. A. No. 2455, ante, p. 21.

L. L. Boone, for Appellants.

Haines & Haines, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

Appeal from a judgment foreclosing the lien of a street assessment. The questions involved are the same as those disposed of in Gay v. Engebretsen, (L. A. No. 2455), ante, p. 21, [109 Pac. 876], and the authority of that case requires an affirmance of the judgment.

Judgment affirmed.
